INTRODUCTION

In today’s digital world, digital literacy is an essential skill for students to effectively use technology for academic and professional purposes. This project aims to develop a practical understanding of digital tools, online platforms, and responsible online behavior.

The project consists of five tasks, including creating an infographic, building a digital portfolio, exploring coding and collaboration platforms, understanding email etiquette, and studying cybercrime awareness. Each task focuses on developing important skills required for effective digital communication and online presence.

Through this project, I gained experience in using tools like Canva, GitHub, LinkedIn, and Google Forms. It also helped me understand the importance of maintaining a professional online identity and practicing safe internet usage. Overall, this project improved my confidence in using digital platforms efficiently and responsibly.



TASK 1 – DIGITAL LITERACY INFOGRAPHIC

For this task, I designed a Digital Literacy Awareness infographic using Canva, a user-friendly design platform that allows quick creation of professional visuals. It enabled me to organize information clearly using icons, layouts, and color coding.

The infographic covers three key areas: Safe Internet Practices, Email Etiquette, and Professional Online Presence. I included practical points such as using strong passwords, enabling two-factor authentication, writing clear and formal emails, and maintaining a professional LinkedIn profile. The goal was to present essential digital habits in a simple and visually engaging format for students.

The most interesting part of this task was learning how design elements improve clarity and readability. The main challenge was fitting relevant content into a limited space without overcrowding the layout. This required careful selection of information and proper alignment. Overall, this task improved my ability to communicate important ideas effectively through visual design.


TASK 2 – STUDENT DIGITAL PORTFOLIO

For this task, I created and updated my profiles on GitHub, LinkedIn and Research gate . These platforms are widely used for showcasing skills, building professional connections, and engaging with the academic community.

GitHub is mainly used to store and manage projects, allowing me to build a portfolio of my technical work over time. LinkedIn helps in creating a professional identity, connecting with peers and industry professionals, and exploring career opportunities. ResearchGate is focused on academic research, where students and researchers can share papers and follow developments in their field.

Over the next four years, I plan to regularly update my GitHub with projects, improve my LinkedIn profile by adding skills and achievements, and use ResearchGate to explore research work related to aerospace engineering. This will help me build a strong digital presence and prepare for internships and future career opportunities.


