TASK 4 – COMMUNICATION SCENARIO

A common example of poor digital communication is when a student sends an informal and unclear email to a professor or internship coordinator requesting an extension or opportunity. For instance, the email may lack a proper subject line, use casual language like “Hey,” and fail to clearly explain the purpose. In some cases, important documents like an SOP are also poorly written or not attached properly. As a result, the recipient may ignore the email or misunderstand the request, leading to missed opportunities or loss of marks.

This situation could have been handled better by following basic email etiquette. The student should have used a clear subject line, a formal greeting, and a structured message explaining the request politely and concisely. Proper attachment of documents and a respectful sign-off would increase the chances of receiving a positive response. This highlights the importance of clear and professional digital communication.


TASK 5 – CYBERCRIME AWARENESS (Case Study)
For this task, I studied UPI and online payment fraud, which is one of the most common cybercrimes affecting students. UPI fraud occurs when attackers trick users into approving payments or sharing sensitive information. In a typical case, a student receives a call or message from someone pretending to be a bank official or an online buyer. The attacker builds trust and then sends a payment request or QR code, asking the student to approve it to receive money. However, approving the request actually transfers money from the student’s account.

This type of fraud usually targets students and new users who are not fully aware of how digital payment systems work. The consequences include immediate financial loss, difficulty in recovering the money, and mental stress. This case study highlights how simple mistakes, such as trusting unknown sources or not understanding UPI functions, can lead to serious problems. It shows the importance of awareness and careful handling of online transactions.


TASK 5 – REFLECTION (100–150 words)
While researching cybercrime, I was surprised by how easily people fall victim to scams like UPI fraud due to small mistakes and lack of awareness. Many attacks do not involve complex hacking but instead rely on tricking users into trusting fake messages or calls. I realized that even a simple action like approving a payment request without proper understanding can lead to financial loss.
This task made me more cautious about my online activities. One habit I will change is carefully verifying any payment request or link before taking action. I will also avoid sharing any sensitive information and stay alert while using digital platforms. Overall, this task helped me understand that awareness and responsible behavior are key to staying safe online.

